I am using the standalone version. Java 1.6. It is on Solaris running tomcat.
If we use Jira internationally-in that, we have offices around the world and people go between offices, we have an issue if users have logins that exist to do this in multiple domains. The passwords may or may not be the same. The question is is it possible for the authentication to not exit on the first domain it finds with user if authentication fails and instead have it work in a findall manner from the top of the tree through all OUs? For example, if you have a user EUROPE\eurcew and CARYNT\eurcew because the user goes from the United States to Europe, and he is configured to require search all domains under Administration->Browse Users, it will attempt to authenticate him against EUROPE and CARYNT domain. If a positive comes back for either, he is authenticated. I suppose you could have three options: Default, All Domains, and a textbox where you can specify a domain as well, which would be even better.
